        <num>CC 602</num>
        <heading>602.  Set off against damages</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 602.  Set off against damages.
The usufructuary may set off against damages due to the owner for the destruction or deterioration of the property subject to the usufruct the value of improvements that cannot be removed, provided they were made in accordance with Article 558.</p>
        </content>
